data.title: got myself a private tour of the restricted areas of late Iraqi leader #SaddamHussein’s summer palace in Babylon. all i can say is…...
data.meta_description:
2,447 likes, 24 comments - heyrozz on March 11, 2024: "got myself a private tour of the restricted areas of late Iraqi leader #SaddamHussein’s summer palace in Babylon. all i can say is… Saddam’s got style.

Saddam thought of himself as more important than the Babylonian kings of yore so he had his palace built on higher ground overlooking the ancient city of Babylon. these days its a hollow ruin that locals love to hang out in for picnics, a casual game of football in the palace’s large halls, and the occasional graduation photoshoot.

im in love with the marble, the decorative wood details, the space, and just general layout of the entire building. i would kill to see it during its glory years.

interested in visiting Iraq? with ISIS strongholds totally eradicated within the country theres no safer time than now. hit up my pal Shane at @rockyroadtravel for a sample itinerary.

#rozziniraq
#babylon
#solofemaletravel
#shotoniphone15promax

.".
